import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate in the dataset?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['id'], data['rate'])
    plt.xlabel('id')
    plt.ylabel('rate')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between id and rate?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    average_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    plt.axhline(y=average_rate, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average Rate: {average_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average rate in the dataset?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    missing_values = data.isnull().sum()
    missing_values.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Are there any missing values in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
